  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In this study, investigators wanted to investigate the effect of volatile anesthesia and&#xD;
      total intravenous anesthesia (TIVA) on ecchymosis, edema, and intraoperative bleeding in&#xD;
      rhinoplasty.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Routine monitorization (blood pressure, pulse, oxygen saturation with pulse oximetry and&#xD;
      electrocardiogram) will be applied to all patients taken into the operation room.&#xD;
&#xD;
      In Group P (TIVA), induction of anesthesia will be achieved with 2 mg/kg propofol, 0.6 mg/kg&#xD;
      rocuronium, and 1 μ / kg fentanyl. Propofol and remifentanil will be used in the continuation&#xD;
      of anesthesia.&#xD;
&#xD;
      In Group S (Volatile), anesthesia will be induced with 2 mg / kg propofol, 0.6 mg / kg&#xD;
      rocuronium and 1 μ / kg fentanyl. 50% nitrous oxide + 50% oxygen and 2% sevoflurane will be&#xD;
      used in the continuation of anesthesia.&#xD;
&#xD;
      All patients will receive 2 ml/kg/hour Ringer's lactate solution during the operation.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
